Nebraska Emergency Management Agency/FEMA

Click here to view the DR 4420 NE/Severe winter storm, straight-line winds and flooding Fact Sheet published April 11, 2019.

Residents and business owners in Antelope, Boyd, Burt, Cuming, Hall, Howard, Madison, Nance, Pierce, Platte, Saline and Stanton counties may now apply for Individual Assistance from FEMA for losses resulting from the severe winter storm, straight-line winds and flooding March 9-April 1, 2019.

Boone, Buffalo, Butler, Cass, Colfax, Custer, Dodge, Douglas, Knox, Nemaha, Richardson, Sarpy, Saunders, Thurston and Washington counties and the Santee Sioux Nation were previously designated for FEMA Individual Assistance.

Region 3 Behavioral Health Services

Region 3 Behavioral Health Services has the responsibility to coordinate the mental health component of disaster assistance and relief efforts throughout the 22 county area of Region 3.

We work with the county Emergency Managers of those counties impacted by recent flooding to provide resources to help individuals and families access the resources they need.

Every disaster has a mental health component as the psychological stress and distress associated with dealing with the devastation of the flooding, loss of livestock, equipment, usable farm land, homes, buildings, and personal property surfaces.

This psychological stress is a normal reaction to an abnormal situation, but can be overwhelming. Nebraskans are a strong bunch of people who may find it difficult to reach for help, but help is so important and can be life-saving. Click here for details.

Hall County GIS Department:
Flood Event Viewer

The Hall County GIS Department has developed a Web-based GIS application that shows the county roads impacted by the flooding.

In the Sheriff's Department section you can also find info on: Most Wanted fugitives, Arrest Warrants, Sex Offenders, as well as the daily Media Reports. You can find all of these tools and more on the [Sheriff's Department Main Page] including the Annual Report.
